./state/artifacts/20260505T162122-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:1329:./state/evaluation.llm.json:1:{"decision":"not_done","recommend_promotion":false,"confidence":0.78,"summary":"The persistence slice is mostly implemented and the recorded required gates passed, but I would not promote conservatively because the schema does not fully cover the PRD-backed endpoint-management data shape. The current Prisma models omit endpoint title and response-case priority/case-level delay/error fields that the PRD describes for MVP endpoint creation/editing and exact-match cases.","satisfied_exit_criteria":["`npm run db:prepare` is wired to create the data directory, apply Prisma migrations, generate Prisma Client, and run endpoint seed defaults; the provided deterministic check reports it passing.","Repeatability is covered by `tests/unit/db-prepare.test.ts`, which runs `db:prepare` twice against an isolated SQLite database and verifies singular endpoint, parameter, and response-case seed rows.","The schema includes immutable endpoint IDs, endpoint names, descriptions, enabled state, ordered parameters, response cases, default response fields, delete codes, timestamps, and endpoint-level basic failure config fields.","`docs/generated/db-schema.md` matches the implemented Prisma models and seed defaults.","The implementation stays inside the persistence foundation scope and does not add unrelated UI, MCP, REST, Basic Auth, OAuth, or reset behavior."],"missing_requirements":["Endpoint `title` is missing from the Prisma schema and generated DB documentation even though the PRD create/edit endpoint model includes it.","ResponseCase lacks `priority`, `delayMs`, and case-level error fields described by the PRD response-case model; this may force later tasks to change persistence rather than build on it."],"human_review_triggers":["Implementation may contradict or under-cover the PRD-backed persistence shape required by the endpoint-tool-management feature front."]}
